        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="45" name="Message" rows="6" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
I am an ex-rogue.  On the safehouse there is a passworded board where only certified rogues can go, you have to be verified in game by a "warden" to get the password.  On that board they place things that they dont want other people to know like best places to pickpocket from groups, etc.  


I think we should do this for necros.  I know some of us have been thinking about it for a long time,  the eye of zomm / multipet issue could have been kept secret if it were like this.

We would have to PROMISE to let NO ONE know the password, or it wouldnt work.


We need to appoint 2 or 3 people from each server to be "gideons", once someone applys for access their gideon checks to make sure that they are in fact a necromancer in game, and then they are given the password.  I personally think there should be a level limit, but I dont know what the level limit should be, as I dont want to alienate some of our lower level player base.  Its all open to discussion now.


The most important thing to make this work, other than secrecy, is UNITY.  We dont need a constant flame fest here.  We need to help each other out when someone asks questions.


Please post any comments, or if you would like to become a gideon.

I will be out of town for 3 - 4 days, and will get the board started as soon as I get back.  If someone could please keep the thread bumped until then, I would HIGHLY appreciate it.


Thanks for your time.

